SUMMARY:

Radio OS and all derivatives must remain open source under GPL-3.0.

You are free to:
• Use Radio OS for any purpose (commercial, personal, research)
• Modify Radio OS for your needs
• Distribute modified versions
• Run Radio OS as a hosted service

With the condition that:
• You share the source code of your modifications under GPL-3.0
• If you distribute it, you include this license
• If you run a modified version as a service, you must make source available

This ensures Radio OS stays free and hackable forever, while respecting
the original author's IP through copyleft.

